metadata.name: Slice and shrink #19
metadata.description:
A study of how shapes could respond to each other.


---
Algorithm

Inspired by a serie of François Morellet, Pi et plis, 2008 (Pi and folds), the initial action is to divide a plan by random lines. This cutting process works by detecting collisions between the lines. Having noticed that sometimes the cuts are not homogeneous and create very stretched shapes, I added an optional step of pre-cutting the base rectangle from a grid. 

The second main step is to shrink each polygon obtained in the first step. We find this way of entangling shapes in many works of Vera Molnár, who skillfully used this compositional process.
Since these shapes are quite basic and mainly concave, we can use the interior angle to move the corner point inside, to do this we calculate each angle of the vertex of the polygon (from the previous, current and next vertex clockwise), with this angle we can move the point along the bisector of the angle. But a limit must be set otherwise the point will meet the opposite segment, this limit is the distance between the point and the centroid of the polygon, beyond a certain threshold the program stops the operation.

The last operation consists in giving a relief, a texture to its shapes, for that the program is going to move points on both sides of the board by slightly curving their trajectory with a Perlin noise, these bands can be horizontal, vertical or diagonal (two possible choices, go down to the right or to the left). 

This step might seem superfluous but it brings a light vibration to this arbitrary and conceptual composition, it comes to support the uncertain character of this arrangement since what is given to see here is the destruction of a rectangle which for me is an archetypal form of the painting. 


---
Features

Pre-cut from a grid: indicates whether the initial composition will be split (>1) or not (1), the values are between 1 and 3 for the columns and 1 and 4 for the rows.

Cuts: the number of random lines that will divide the composition (between 6 and 13)

Initial margin between contours: the initial space between the contours of the same shape, between 14 and 22. Each time the shape is shrunk, this value is multiplied by 0.92. 

Fill slice: three ways to draw polygons
- minimal / 0.2% probability / first contour of each polygon
- solid / 49.9% chance / first and last contour + corner lines 
- complete / 49.9% likelihood / every contour of the shrinking process + corner lines

Stripe margin: the distance between doodled (colored) lines, between 4 and 8. 

Stripe color: the color of the doodled lines (with the Stabilo© reference), 14 possibles choices


---
Capture and plotter drawing 

You can download a PNG or SVG from the live mode, by clicking on the drawing a window will open where you can change the size of the drawing, download a bitmap or vector image. You are free to reproduce the picture, if you decide to reproduce it with a plotter, please note that the colors used are Stabilo© 88 (Fineliners 0.4)


---
Hybrid series

Slice and shrink is part of Hybrid Series, To learn more, open the link in the live mode option window.

metadata.name: Guil's Road Trip #16
metadata.description:
Guil's Road Trip is the second piece in the continued collaborative journey of Guillaume Cornet and Matthew Seremet.

Join us as we cruise through 6 unique natural environments!
[Rocky Shores] [Dotted Desert] [Frozen Forest] [Lush Woodlands] [Rolling Hills] [Moonville]

This generative work is a departure from the cityscapes and architectural designs Guil has been known for. One inspiration to follow this path came from Matt's appreciation for Guil's published children's book: Elephants on Tour (available in multiple languages).


—

The tech behind this project utilizes the highly compressed WEBP image format in order to provide so many full-color options. This format is great, but unfortunately Safari on desktop/laptop must be upgraded to at least version 14 and macOS to at least version 11 Big Sur to use it.

—

To find out more about your GuilCity, copy your unique operation hash and place it at the end of the following url:
• https://roadtrip.guil.city?fxhash=
(for example: https://roadtrip.guil.city?fxhash=ooezL8cffNJGSc4TfNQp3u3WnDpkg8J3zFRczLuumceoYU5QYPs)

—

Keyboard Controls:
[q] - Open .GIF export panel
[u] - Get link to updated version
[space] - Pause

metadata.name: Minimal Scapes #94
metadata.description:
I keep focused and fascinated by minimal compositions and Minimal Scapes is a realization of that exploration as an artist. 

On Minimal Scapes, I recreate several types of hills, mountains, and ground elements on different layers in order to create a sense of depth, also I combine different sky shades and sun sizes, reflecting sunsets & sunrises.

Type of Scapes
Canyon Scape
Mountain Scape
Desert Scape
Ocean Scape

My connection with the earth continues with Minimal Scapes, and it is reflected in the colors that I’ve selected, which very much define which type of scape is minted.

Made with ❤️ & pj5s

By CodeNFT (Clementine Novak)
October 2022

metadata.name: chorégraphie #296
metadata.description:
… divided in two,
like the parent in sound and motion.
yet not exactly the same, I get …


chorégraphie explores the algorithmic characteristics of recursion in audiovisual form.

The algorithm performs a recursive split. At each split stage, space is divided into four different sized quadrants. Each split stage will eventually spawn an oscillator or a synthesizer representing the current properties of recursion in sound. The process is recursively repeated until a maximum recursion depth is reached or an early return condition is met.
Additionally, an initial motion funnction is randomly selected and propageted through the recursion, so that each recursive split stage with move depending on it’s split properties in combination with time.

Click into the piece to start the audio. Each piece can be seeded with a new initial configuration by pressing the ‘s’ key.

© 2022 — Guido Schmidt

Created with:
p5, tone, @thi.ng/color, random

metadata.name: GEN XYZ Das Occult #4265
metadata.description:
A 10k Generative Profile Pic collection
GEN XYZ Das Occult - by culla - @tamccullough

move over cryptopunks
there is a new group on the scene

100% code - not an image composition

A bunch of common palettes
A selection of rare palettes
And a smaller set of ultra rare palettes
However, rarity will be based on what combinations the code produces

The majority of tokens will not have a special trait
However your token might have one or even multiple special traits
But, be aware that only the last special trait added will be listed in the features

Even then, look closely, because not all aspects of the canvas are included in the features. Collectors should still look closely and choose what they like when buying on secondary.

Which team are you on? X or O?

follow culla on twitter for updates. Or maybe __acolyte__

If the non reserved tokens mint out quickly, Access List mints will have 24 hours to mint reserves assigned to those wallets

Thank you for supporting an emerging artist in the generative art space

Access List reserves were given to holders of the following PFP collections created by culla
2x for each Basqunk held
1x for each Inkspunk, TwoFourQunk, V0iD, DeeManz, Punkasso and CR0$$KULL
You would have needed to transfer the above tokens to your mint wallet at the time of the snapshot

share your tokens on social media with #genxyznft
